 Indian Penal Code, Section 107, third paragraph-Abetment, meaning of-Proof that crime charged could not have been committed without the interposition of alleged abettor, if sufficient compliance with the section.
 Criminal Trial-Conduct of shouting by accused during the occurrence-Court not justified in heaping one assumption on another to particular conduct of accused a meaning it does not naturally bear.
 Code of Criminal Procedure, Section 342-Failure of accused to explain her shout in her statement-Adverse inference, if could be drawn-Accused, if could subjected to cross- examination.
 Criminal Trial-Identification parade, a weak type of evidence-Oral testimony of prosecution witness, if should be corroborated by evidence of identification-Accused asking for an identification parade, a circumstance, in his favour.
 
